1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:09,944
This next idea changes everything,  A transactional.id creates a stable identity for the producer across restarts.

2
00:00:09,894 --> 00:00:23,197
The broker fences old producer instances with the same transactional ID by bumping the producer epoch — old instances attempting to write are rejected with ProducerFencedException.

3
00:00:23,197 --> 00:00:27,447
Master this, and you're not just interview-ready.

4
00:00:27,447 --> 00:00:29,644
You're production-ready.

5
00:00:29,644 --> 00:00:31,394
That's rare.

